<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Reparenting_Existing_Levels">Reparenting Existing Levels</span></h3>
<p>For levels you've already made, you can reparent them to your custom Level BP like this:
</p><p><a href="/File:Reparentlevels.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Reparentlevels.jpg" src="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/3/37/Reparentlevels.jpg/500px-Reparentlevels.jpg" width="500" height="169" srcset="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/3/37/Reparentlevels.jpg/750px-Reparentlevels.jpg 1.5x, https://d26ilriwvtzlb.cloudfront.net/3/37/Reparentlevels.jpg 2x" /></a>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Config.2FDefaultEngine.ini">Config/DefaultEngine.ini</span></h3>
<p>You can tell UE4 that you want <b>every new level to start using your custom Level BP</b>!
</p>
<pre>&#160;;---------------- CUSTOM LEVEL BP CLASS ------------------
&#160;;--- new levels will use the new default script actor!!!
 [/Script/Engine.Engine]
&#160;;LevelScriptActorClassName=/Script/Engine.LevelScriptActor
 LevelScriptActorClassName=/Script/Solus.SolusLevelScriptActor
&#160;;----------------------------------------------------------
</pre>
